    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static PeakSet getInstance(double[] mzArray,
                  double[] intensityArray)
        Translate the m/z Array and intensity Array into a set of peaks.

        Notice: the length of two array should be equal.

        Parameters:
        mzArray - if null, return a empty peak set.
        intensityArray - if null, return a empty peak set.

      • splitWindow

        public List<PeakSet> splitWindow(int splitSize)
        split the whole peaks into list of subsets. Each subset m/z length less than or equal splitSize. subset is (startMZ, endMZ], endMz - startMz <= splitSize.

      • subSet

        public PeakSet subSet(double mz,
             double interval)
        Create a subset of peak set. The range is [m/z - interval, m/z + interval].
        Parameters:
        mz - should be in the range of peak set. that is, [first_peak.m/z, last_peak.m/z]. Otherwise, return empty peak set.
        interval - should great than 0. Otherwise, return empty peak set.

      • getMaxIntensityPeak

        public Peak getMaxIntensityPeak()
        Returns:
        the maximum intensity peak within the peaks window. If more than one peaks, return the first matching peak.
